place.name: CAWKWELL
place.gazetteerText: CAWKWELL, a parish in Horncastle district, Lincoln; 6½ miles SW of Legbourne r. station, and 7 N of Horncastle. Post Town, Scamblesby, under Horncastle. Acres, 540. Real property, £870. Pop., 36. Houses, 7. The property is divided among a few. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £46. Patron, Lord Yarborough. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
